<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - RADIATOR and
        Component INSTALLation - RADIATOR HOSE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>RADIATOR HOSE</title>
        <para>Check radiator hoses prior to installation.</para>
        <para>Place Gates SB clamps on each end of radiator hose to be reconnected. Use the following procedure to
            install Gates SB clamps.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200824" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200824.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200824.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 24. Gates SB Clamp</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove clamp from brace by squeezing band to collapse, then fold in half and remove it from
                cardboard.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200825" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200825.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200825.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. PowerGrip Shrink Clamp Preparation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CARDBOARD REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GATES SB CLAMP</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place clamps over each end of new hose.</para>
            <figure id="f1200826" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200826.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200826.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Radiator Hose And Shrink Clamps</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GATES SB CLAMPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RADIATOR HOSE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position hose over fittings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide clamp over top of fitting bead. (Gates SB clamps have a wider sealing surface than
                conventional clamps and can be positioned over a wide area including the bead without causing leaks.)
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200827" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200827.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200827.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Cross Section Clamp And Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. STEM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Be sure to position so the print on the clamp is facing up (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="g1200824.webp">Figure 24</hotlnk>) and in full view.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply heat as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use standard heat gun with setting on high.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Do not use open flame to apply heat.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Follow heat gun manufacturer's safety procedures.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Do not apply heat to one spot too long. Move gun continuously.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Move heat gun continuously around as much of the clamps surface as possible- 1/3 of the
                    surface minimum.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Although Gates SB clamps are very durable, too much heat can melt them.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Continue until shrinking is complete (printed information on the clamp will turn gray
                    when enough heat has been applied).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the heat source.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check connections to be sure a good seal was made by trying to turn the hose. Hose and clamp
                should not turn when using
                <emph type="bold">reasonable</emph>
                torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace coolant after all other installations have been completed.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When all other installations, surge tank and related components, including charge air cooler
                are installed, start engine and check for leaks. If leaks appear, apply more heat to the Gates SB
                clamps.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
